      "content": "While it is natural to feel better when symptoms disappear, stopping antibiotics early can actually allow surviving bacteria to multiply and become resistant to future treatments. A doctor can often tell if an infection is truly cleared at three days, so the safest path forward is a quick call to your prescriber to confirm your plan. Please consult your healthcare provider before making any changes to your medication, as their guidance is tailored to your specific condition.",
      "source": "target",
