      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even if you feel perfectly healthy and inflammation has subsided, the bacteria causing the infection may not all be dead when symptoms disappear. Continuing the full prescribed course ensures the complete elimination of any remaining bacteria to prevent a relapse or resistance. Relying on internet forums instead of professional medical advice can be dangerous because infections vary significantly in how quickly they resolve. Please contact your doctor for a quick confirmation, as it is far safer than risking a difficult-to-treat infection later.",
      "source": "target",
